I had a really good day at work today so I thought I would share the joy--it was a very productive fun day. It is starting to feel more like old Borders to me, perhaps I am looking through rose colored glasses. Since I decided on my last day I have found myself rather nostalgic for a job I have'nt left yet! I have stuck with the not smoking and have eaten healthy and exercised for a week, so far so good.
http://spikes-grrl.livejournal.com/3764.html

Finally, right? I am really not good at this. It took me 5 minutes to figure out how to add a new post! considering I have'nt touched it since December I guess that is not all too surprising! I just finished working out and I am going to eat something and get ready to go to work. I am in an interesting place mentally right now. I am feeling very strong. I had quit smoking about 6 weeks ago and then i lapsed over vacation (not altogether surprising) but when a friend(with good intentions) mentioned the fact that they could'nt keep up with whether I was smoking or not it made me feel really weak and foolish, and for the first time that was unacceptable to me. I quit the next day and have'nt even wanted one since. It's strange. I just kind of had a revelation that the only thing keeping me from accomplishing any of my goals is me, plain and simple. I had said to my husband around the same time that I could'nt quit until he was ready to, that I could'nt be strong without him. Utter foolishness. There have been cigarettes in the house for the past 3 days and i have'nt really even been tempted. It's odd. The same with exercise and eating healthy. I have always talked a good game and then fallen off the wagon. I am sick of it. I tried to sign up for a weight loss study at UT because I thought having support and structure would keep me on track but I could'nt take part because Jim and I are trying to get pregnant. What better reason to get healthy right? When I told Jim he said forget it, baby is more important than losing weight. It made me start thinking, if a baby is the most important thing to us right now then getting healthy and being strong should be the top priority in my life. Why has'nt it been? because I was weak. And foolish. NO MORE.
